Introduction

Kim Sohee is a South Korean singer and actress under n.CH Entertainment, member of the girl duo Atlantis Kisune. She gained prominence through her participation in the popular television competition, Produce 101, in 2016.

Following her appearance on the show, she became a member of several project groups, including C.I.V.A, I.B.I, and Girls Next Door. After these groups disbanded, Sohee embarked on a solo career, releasing her debut mini-album titled “The Filette” in 2017.

On the 8th of October, 2019, she entered into an exclusive agreement with n.CH Entertainment. Subsequently, it was revealed that she would become a member of the girl group NATURE.
